{
  "texts": [
    "The signature detection stage may require knowledge of the original content.",
    "In this case, we say that a watermarking algorithm is non-blind.",
    "Contrary, if the watermark is recovered without resorting to the comparison between the original media and the marked one, the watermarking algorithm is blind.If the signature contains a sequence of N bits, it can be read from the marked media.",
    "In this case, the watermarking algorithm is called multi-bit watermarking.",
    "However, in the 0-bit watermarking, the detector tries to decide whether a known signature is present in the given media."
  ]
}